menu "nff SDK"

config NFF_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_S
    int "Heartbeat publish interval (seconds)"
    default 30
    range 5 300
    help
        How often the device publishes a retained heartbeat to
        nff/devices/{id}/heartbeat. Lower values improve presence
        detection speed at the cost of slightly more MQTT traffic.

config NFF_LOG_LINES
    int "RTC pre-crash log buffer size (lines)"
    default 32
    range 8 64
    help
        Number of log lines kept in RTC memory across software resets.
        These are included verbatim in crash reports. Each line is
        NFF_LOG_LINE_LEN (128) bytes.

config NFF_NONCE_RING_SIZE
    int "Command nonce ring buffer size"
    default 16
    range 4 64
    help
        Number of command nonces remembered for replay prevention.
        When the ring is full, the oldest nonce is evicted. Set
        higher if your device receives many commands per hour.

config NFF_TIMESTAMP_WINDOW_S
    int "Command timestamp acceptance window (seconds)"
    default 300
    range 60 3600
    help
        Commands with timestamps older than this many seconds from the
        device's current time are rejected. Requires SNTP to be
        synchronised before nff_connect() for meaningful protection.

config NFF_OTA_CONFIRM_TIMEOUT_S
    int "OTA confirm window before automatic rollback (seconds)"
    default 60
    range 10 600
    help
        After an OTA, the new image runs on probation. If it does not
        reconnect to the broker (and pass any registered health check)
        within this window, the device automatically reverts to the
        previous image and reports "rolled_back".

config NFF_OTA_MAX_TRIAL_BOOTS
    int "Unconfirmed OTA trial boots tolerated before rollback"
    default 3
    range 2 10
    help
        Crash-loop guard. A freshly-flashed image that reboots this many
        times without confirming itself healthy is treated as bad and
        rolled back. A healthy image confirms within seconds of the
        first boot, so this only trips on a crash loop.

config NFF_OTA_MAX_DL_RETRIES
    int "OTA download attempts before giving up"
    default 4
    range 1 16
    help
        A transient TLS stall mid-download is retried with an HTTP Range
        header from where it stopped (the SHA-256 context is kept in RAM),
        so a dropped transfer does not restart from byte 0. This caps the
        number of resume attempts per OTA. In-session only — not persisted
        across reboots.

config NFF_OTA_DL_RETRY_BACKOFF_MS
    int "Delay between OTA resume attempts (ms)"
    default 2000
    range 0 30000
    help
        How long to wait before retrying a stalled OTA download.

config NFF_OTA_MIN_HEAP_FLOOR
    int "OTA health gate minimum free-heap floor (bytes)"
    default 20000
    range 0 200000
    help
        A freshly-flashed image is not committed unless min_free_heap stays
        above this floor (plus the soak window below and any registered
        health check). Catches an image that connects but is leaking heap.

config NFF_OTA_MIN_HEALTHY_MS
    int "OTA health gate soak window (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 0 60000
    help
        The new image must remain healthy (connected + above the heap floor
        + any registered health check) continuously for this long before it
        is committed. Catches an image that connects then degrades. Must be
        comfortably less than NFF_OTA_CONFIRM_TIMEOUT_S * 1000.

endmenu
